ents_url": "https://api.github.com/users/drpngx/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/drpngx/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 13, "created_at": "2018-08-08T19:23:13Z", "updated_at": "2018-08-24T17:33:22Z", "closed_at": "2018-08-17T20:43:54Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/21486", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21486", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21486.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/21486.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>The old implementation of elastic average optimizer does not partitioned variables, support optimizer like AdamOptimizer which will create global variables like beta_1, beta2.</p>\n<p>Main changes:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>supports partitioned variables</li>\n<li>support more optimizers, e.g., Adam/RMSProp</li>\n<li>add a saver to save the values in the global_center_variable<br>\nAs it turns out the global model is better than the local worker. To allow chief worker save the global values, a mapping logic is added.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Verifications I have done:  Cifar10 on AlexNet/MobileNetV2 and other internal models.<br>\nAll Results shows better performance and precision.</p>\n<p>Related Item<br>\n<a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"251825810\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/12472\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/12472/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/12472\">#12472</a>: Feature request: EASGD<br>\n<a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=184424\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/ali01\">@ali01</a>, <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=8096033\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/jinxin0924\">@jinxin0924</a>, <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=7132307\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/tmulc18\">@tmulc18</a> Could you kindly help on review the changes?</p>", "body_text": "The old implementation of elastic average optimizer does not partitioned variables, support optimizer like AdamOptimizer which will create global variables like beta_1, beta2.\nMain changes:\n\nsupports partitioned variables\nsupport more optimizers, e.g., Adam/RMSProp\nadd a saver to save the values in the global_center_variable\nAs it turns out the global model is better than the local worker. To allow chief worker save the global values, a mapping logic is added.\n\nVerifications I have done:  Cifar10 on AlexNet/MobileNetV2 and other internal models.\nAll Results shows better performance and precision.\nRelated Item\n#12472: Feature request: EASGD\n@ali01, @jinxin0924, @tmulc18 Could you kindly help on review the changes?", "body": "The old implementation of elastic average optimizer does not partitioned variables, support optimizer like AdamOptimizer which will create global variables like beta_1, beta2.\r\n\r\nMain changes:\r\n1. supports partitioned variables\r\n2. support more optimizers, e.g., Adam/RMSProp\r\n3. add a saver to save the values in the global_center_variable\r\n    As it turns out the global model is better than the local worker. To allow chief worker save the global values, a mapping logic is added.\r\n\r\nVerifications I have done:  Cifar10 on AlexNet/MobileNetV2 and other internal models.\r\nAll Results shows better performance and precision.\r\n\r\nRelated Item\r\n#12472: Feature request: EASGD\r\n@ali01, @jinxin0924, @tmulc18 Could you kindly help on review the changes?\r\n"}